element_texts.text:
Hecht, Mike
[1978]
10
(At me, I presume) into the beautiful, beautiful, Chicago night.
Eventually a street car came along -- now why do fathers have to be so humorless I thought.. and I got home ... and you know, I never had the courage to go back?
And that's a shame. Cause she was a lovely girl. and we liked each other. And we were good for each other.
[lines redacted]
And how often does a girl get an honest answer from a boy that's taken a fancy to her... the very first time.
